34:24.690 --> 34:27.775
<i>Everything You Need
Is in Your Own Backyard?</i>

34:27.860 --> 34:31.196
- I think it was a French book.
- Yeah, that wasn't a book.

34:31.280 --> 34:33.407
- That was a book.
- No, it was a cartoon.

34:33.489 --> 34:34.992
- The fuck out of here.
- No, it was a cartoon.

34:35.074 --> 34:37.286
- Right, Helene?
- Fuck youse both.

34:37.369 --> 34:38.495
Should we bring in the FBI
at this point?

34:38.579 --> 34:40.873
- That's the worst thing we could do.
- Why is that?

34:40.914 --> 34:42.748
'Cause I don't wanna see Cheese
kill Amanda

34:42.833 --> 34:44.126
after he opens a bag
full of newspapers.

34:44.208 --> 34:45.627
It's kidnapping.

34:45.710 --> 34:49.339
- I don't see a note. You see a note?
- Nope. No note.

34:49.422 --> 34:51.675
We're investigating
a missing children's case, here.

34:51.717 --> 34:55.137
Kidnapping has nothing to do with it.
Fastest way to get Amanda home

34:55.219 --> 34:58.182
is go to Cheese,
swap the money for her and walk away.

34:58.265 --> 35:01.727
- Plain and simple.
- Do you know Cheese?

35:01.768 --> 35:05.230
Knew his brother better, Jude.
He was a sweet kid.

35:05.314 --> 35:07.274
Cheese went another way.

35:08.317 --> 35:11.695
- He wouldn't hurt her, right?
- Ask Ray.

35:11.778 --> 35:13.572
All right, listen.
All he cares about is his money.

35:13.655 --> 35:16.074
If he gets it back...
He's not gonna hurt Amanda.

35:16.116 --> 35:19.661
Just keep your mouth shut, okay?
We'll get her back. It'll be fine.

35:19.745 --> 35:22.039
- Oh, you're gonna talk to him?
- Yeah, that's the idea.

35:22.080 --> 35:24.249
Okay. Well, tell him I'm sorry, all right?

35:24.333 --> 35:27.002
I mean, he knows me,
just tell him I apologize.

35:27.085 --> 35:29.922
Yeah, I'm sure that'll fix everything.
Just take her home.

35:29.963 --> 35:33.091
- We'll take care of this, all right?
- We'll meet you over there.

35:33.175 --> 35:34.593
I'm hungry.

35:34.635 --> 35:35.928
All right. I'll get you something, Helene.

35:36.011 --> 35:37.638
No, her.

35:37.721 --> 35:39.681
That's what she said to me
right before I put her to bed.

35:39.765 --> 35:42.267
She said, "I'm hungry."
I mean, they fed her, right?

35:42.351 --> 35:44.436
She's not still hungry?

35:45.812 --> 35:47.105
I don't know.

36:34.319 --> 36:36.154
I know I fucked up.

36:37.281 --> 36:38.490
I just want my daughter back.

36:38.574 --> 36:42.369
I swear to God,
I won't use no drugs no more.

36:42.452 --> 36:44.288
I won't even go out,
I'll be fucking straight.

36:44.329 --> 36:45.956
Cross my heart.

36:47.249 --> 36:49.293
It's all right.
We're gonna find her, Helene.

36:49.376 --> 36:51.420
You have to. You promise?

36:53.297 --> 36:56.216
Yeah. I'm gonna try. I will.

36:57.551 --> 37:00.762
Promise. You have to promise me.

37:02.514 --> 37:03.807
I promise.

37:08.812 --> 37:09.897
All right.

37:27.289 --> 37:28.290
<i>Where do you
think you're going?</i>

37:28.373 --> 37:29.374
<i>Talk to Cheese.</i>

37:29.458 --> 37:31.126
<i>No, you're not.
No, get back in the car.</i>

37:31.210 --> 37:33.754
<i>No, that's a mistake.
He's never gonna talk to a badge.</i>

37:33.837 --> 37:35.214
<i>No. No way.
It's too important.</i>

37:35.297 --> 37:36.840
<i>You wanna get the girl back, or not?</i>

37:37.341 --> 37:39.009
<i>I know him.
If there's a deal to be brokered,</i>

37:39.092 --> 37:41.178
- we're the ones who can do it.
- No, me and Nick are handling this.

37:41.220 --> 37:42.221
Get back in the car.

37:42.304 --> 37:45.057
Guys, you two go in there
and negotiate a ransom for a little girl,

37:45.140 --> 37:48.560
then it is the FBI.
'Cause it's kidnapping.

37:48.602 --> 37:49.770
All you're gonna do
is scare him.

37:49.853 --> 37:52.564
The more you scare him,
the worse it is for her.

37:57.319 --> 37:59.071
All right. Go ahead.

37:59.571 --> 38:03.867
Just fucking relax, sit tight. I know him.
I'm gonna take care of it.

38:03.909 --> 38:05.410
Good luck.

38:11.792 --> 38:13.544
It's been a long time.

38:16.588 --> 38:18.799
No. I quit.

38:25.889 --> 38:28.267
I'm gonna talk some private shit.

38:29.852 --> 38:34.398
- Don't wait, but don't get too far.
- You know I'll be right here.

38:36.483 --> 38:38.861
Bitches love the cheddar.

38:44.783 --> 38:47.870
- How you been, Chris?
- Better than you.

38:50.289 --> 38:52.374
Yeah. Good to hear it.

38:52.457 --> 38:55.544
- Fuck you.
- Man, be cool.

38:55.627 --> 38:59.506
It's been too long not to see a fool.

38:59.590 --> 39:01.592
I grant you audience.

39:02.718 --> 39:03.719
Go.

39:05.220 --> 39:08.348
We found what you
were looking for in Chelsea.

39:09.641 --> 39:11.518
What I care about Chelsea?

39:11.602 --> 39:14.813
'Cause one of the idiots
that robbed you lived there.

39:14.855 --> 39:16.815
What idiot?

39:16.857 --> 39:20.944
The one that you and Chris
beat with a pipe and shot in the chest.

39:22.905 --> 39:26.116
I don't know about nobody getting kill.

39:27.075 --> 39:29.828
But if somebody rob me
and end up dead...

39:30.996 --> 39:35.042
Well, you know, life is a motherfucker.

39:37.544 --> 39:41.757
Cheese, we got your money.
It was buried in Ray's backyard.

39:43.175 --> 39:46.678
We wanna give it back to you
in exchange for Amanda McCready.

39:46.845 --> 39:50.140
The two police outside
are the only other people who know.

39:50.182 --> 39:52.643
No one gives a fuck
about what you did.

39:52.726 --> 39:54.853
I mean, I didn't even
like Ray that much.

39:54.937 --> 39:57.689
You're gonna get your money,
the mother gets her daughter back,

39:57.773 --> 39:59.733
and we'll say we found the kid
in the bushes, or whatever.

40:00.943 --> 40:02.903
It's either this, real quiet,

40:02.986 --> 40:05.197
or it's a thousand fucking cops
kicking your door in,

40:05.280 --> 40:07.783
putting their fat knees in your neck.

40:11.245 --> 40:12.496
Hold up.

40:14.831 --> 40:16.917
Whoa. Whoa.

40:18.210 --> 40:19.837
What the fuck is this?

40:21.129 --> 40:22.714
Lift up your shirt.

40:23.882 --> 40:26.635
- Come on, man.
- Motherfucker, you heard me.

40:27.386 --> 40:29.096
Lift up your shirt.

40:30.138 --> 40:33.684
- It ain't like that, Cheese.
- My CC, I ain't down with you.

40:34.017 --> 40:35.769
Lift up your shirt.

40:42.067 --> 40:43.610
You, too, baby.
Ain't no gender immunity.

40:43.694 --> 40:45.195
Let me see some tit.

40:51.535 --> 40:54.121
Don't ever come in my spot like that.

40:57.416 --> 40:59.042
You got my money,

40:59.126 --> 41:02.921
you leave that shit in the mailbox
on your ass way out, you feel me?

41:03.046 --> 41:04.923
Some other motherfuckers
let fool rob on them.

41:05.007 --> 41:07.217
I don't play scrimmage.

41:07.301 --> 41:09.553
But I don't fuck with no kids.

41:12.848 --> 41:18.270
And if that girl only hope is you,
well, I pray for her,

41:18.353 --> 41:20.230
'cause she's gone, baby.

41:21.356 --> 41:22.524
Gone.

41:32.951 --> 41:34.995
Cheese, if you ever
disrespect her again like that,

41:35.078 --> 41:37.664
I'm gonna pull your fucking card.

41:37.748 --> 41:38.874
Okay?

41:44.755 --> 41:47.382
So you're saying you didn't do it, fine.

41:47.466 --> 41:50.511
We'll take your money,
and we'll be on our way.

41:51.470 --> 41:53.472
But if it turns out you're lying,

41:53.555 --> 41:56.225
I'm going to spend every nickel
of that money to fuck you up.

41:56.308 --> 41:57.976
I'm gonna bribe cops to go after you,

41:58.060 --> 42:00.521
I'm gonna pay guys
to go after your weak fucking crew,

42:00.604 --> 42:03.690
and I'm gonna tell everyone I know
that you're a CI and a rat.

42:03.774 --> 42:05.859
And I know a lot of people.

42:06.485 --> 42:08.612
And after that, you're gonna wish
you had listened to me,

42:08.695 --> 42:11.448
'cause your shitty, pool-hall,
crime-syndicate headquarters

42:11.532 --> 42:12.908
is gonna get raided.

42:12.991 --> 42:15.494
And your doped-up bitches
are gonna get sent back to Laos,

42:15.577 --> 42:17.996
and this fucking retard right here
is gonna be testifying against you

42:18.080 --> 42:20.499
for a reduced sentence while you're
getting cornholed in your cell

42:20.541 --> 42:22.251
by a gang of crackers.

42:24.419 --> 42:26.338
'Cause from what I heard,

42:26.421 --> 42:29.716
you guys that get sent up Concord
for killing kids,

42:29.800 --> 42:31.593
life a motherfucker.

42:42.980 --> 42:46.400
If I see you again,
I'm gonna get discourteous on you.

42:58.745 --> 43:00.914
And get that sausage off my lawn.

43:01.832 --> 43:04.543
- Well, what happened?
- He said he didn't know anything,

43:04.626 --> 43:07.379
but if you had his money,
you could put it in his mailbox.

43:07.462 --> 43:10.382
- That's what he told you?
- That's it.

43:10.424 --> 43:12.426
Nothing else?

43:12.509 --> 43:15.846
Yeah. He said that he wanted
you two off his lawn.

43:17.264 --> 43:19.183
I thought you said
you knew this fucking guy.

43:19.266 --> 43:21.476
Half the guys he knows
are degenerates.

43:21.560 --> 43:23.187
Yeah, you know
what the other half are?

43:23.228 --> 43:26.273
- What?
- Cops. Don't hold it against me.

43:26.899 --> 43:31.236
No, no. I won't hold it against you.

43:32.696 --> 43:35.115
You know what I'll hold against you?

43:35.199 --> 43:39.703
We had one chance to make this deal.
You said you knew him.

43:39.745 --> 43:42.748
You said you could do it
and you fucked it up.

43:43.415 --> 43:45.792
Now I gotta get a warrant for a tap,
start surveillance,

43:45.876 --> 43:47.753
hope to Christ we get lucky.

43:47.794 --> 43:49.880
You know, if Amanda
dies because of this,

43:51.965 --> 43:53.842
I won't have to hold it against you.

43:55.135 --> 43:58.555
You'll hold it against yourself
for a long, long time.

44:25.123 --> 44:27.334
Hope we didn't fuck this up.

44:36.802 --> 44:39.054
- Yeah.
- Cheese called in.

44:39.137 --> 44:41.974
<i>Says he'll take the deal with Amanda,
but he wants to go tonight.</i>

44:42.015 --> 44:44.643
- Great.
- Well, it is and it isn't.

44:44.726 --> 44:47.437
They record calls at the station now.

44:47.479 --> 44:50.065
<i>- Jack got a hold of the transcript.
- What does that mean?</i>

44:50.148 --> 44:53.193
It means our badges are
basically fucking forfeit at this point.

44:53.277 --> 44:55.153
<i>He wants you both down here, now.</i>

44:55.195 --> 44:57.322
Oh, and, hey, Cheese said
he left something in a mailbox

44:57.406 --> 44:59.783
to prove that he's got Amanda.

45:21.221 --> 45:25.309
This is a transcript of a recorded call
that came in this morning.

45:28.520 --> 45:30.647
Care to read the highlighted portion?

45:32.816 --> 45:34.151
Aloud?

45:35.235 --> 45:36.570
Uh.

45:37.696 --> 45:42.075
Bitch,
you better have my money.

45:45.037 --> 45:47.206
"Detective Bressant: Who is this?

45:47.247 --> 45:50.834
"The caller:
You know who the fuck this is, fool...

45:50.876 --> 45:53.378
"Creole curse words.
If you want that girl back,

45:53.462 --> 45:55.923
"you need to meet me up
Quincy tonight.

45:56.006 --> 45:58.509
"Fuck around for a minute
and I'll throw that girl in the lake."

45:58.592 --> 46:02.179
The lake he refers to is the water
in the abandoned quarry.

46:03.555 --> 46:07.935
Detective Bressant goes on to make
an unauthorized ransom arrangement

46:08.018 --> 46:11.730
to exchange Amanda McCready
for $ 130,000 tonight

46:11.813 --> 46:13.857
in just that location.

46:14.858 --> 46:18.445
After some discussion,
Detective Bressant was kind enough

46:18.529 --> 46:20.197
to produce this.

46:20.280 --> 46:22.449
Recognize it?

46:22.533 --> 46:25.619
The four of you have involved me
in an illegal activity

46:25.702 --> 46:29.206
without my knowledge or consent,
and I don't fucking appreciate it.

46:29.248 --> 46:32.751
- You don't have to be a part of it, sir.
- The hell I don't.

46:32.835 --> 46:34.586
If I delay this now, after this agreement,

46:34.628 --> 46:37.339
I just further endanger
the life of that child.

46:37.422 --> 46:40.259
Does that sound like something
you expect me to do?

46:40.342 --> 46:41.677
No, sir.

46:42.511 --> 46:44.179
I went in there. I'll accept responsibility.

46:44.263 --> 46:46.098
You'll accept nothing!

46:46.390 --> 46:48.892
Don't come in here
trying to get noble, boy.

46:51.103 --> 46:52.896
Let me see that note.

47:00.112 --> 47:01.238
My God.

47:04.449 --> 47:06.451
He wants to separate us.

47:06.535 --> 47:09.246
The note instructs you guys to be
on the east side and wait for Amanda,

47:09.329 --> 47:12.666
me and Nick to be at the clearing
by the edge with the money.

47:12.749 --> 47:15.544
Once Amanda's turned over to you,
you give us a call on the radio,

47:15.627 --> 47:17.421
we turn over the cash.

47:18.839 --> 47:21.633
- Who's he likely to bring with him?
- Chris Mullen.

47:21.717 --> 47:23.844
He was at the club
when we made the offer.

47:23.927 --> 47:25.554
What do you know about him?

47:25.637 --> 47:28.557
It was probably him
who killed Ray for Cheese.

47:28.640 --> 47:29.808
If I had to guess.

47:29.892 --> 47:32.644
All right.
Nobody else knows about this, right?

47:32.728 --> 47:35.147
- I don't know.
- Yes?

47:35.230 --> 47:39.318
I'm asking if keeping it quiet is better
for Amanda or is it better for us?

47:40.652 --> 47:43.697
Do you have any children,
Miss Gennaro?

47:43.780 --> 47:45.324
No, sir.

47:46.825 --> 47:51.330
My only child was murdered.
She was 12. Did you hear about it?

47:53.165 --> 47:54.374
What you probably didn't hear,

47:54.458 --> 47:55.667
and what I hope
you never have to deal with,

47:55.751 --> 47:59.171
Miss Gennaro, is what that feels like.
What I have to deal with.

48:00.047 --> 48:03.800
Knowing that my little girl likely died

48:03.842 --> 48:06.470
crying out for me
to come and save her.

48:07.429 --> 48:09.056
And I never did.

48:09.806 --> 48:16.063
My little girl died afraid and alone
in a shallow ditch bank

48:16.146 --> 48:19.691
by the side of the road
not 10 minutes from my house.

48:23.111 --> 48:25.948
I know what it feels like to lose a child.

48:28.575 --> 48:31.745
Now, damn it, you force my hand

48:31.828 --> 48:34.122
and then you question
the way I handle it.

48:34.206 --> 48:36.375
No one's questioning you, sir.

48:36.458 --> 48:39.211
I honor my child with this division.

48:40.420 --> 48:43.340
So that no parent
has to go through what I've known.

48:44.383 --> 48:46.260
This child.

48:49.388 --> 48:51.056
That's all I care about.

48:51.932 --> 48:53.976
I'm gonna bring her home.

49:09.741 --> 49:12.369
Why'd he bring us all the way up here?

49:14.580 --> 49:17.165
I don't know. It's big. It's dark.
It's easy to get away.

49:17.249 --> 49:18.292
No.

49:20.961 --> 49:22.921
They're gonna kill her.

49:46.320 --> 49:50.449
This asshole could've found
some level fucking ground somewhere.

49:50.532 --> 49:54.536
This is where we part ways.
You guys'll be on top of that cliff.

49:54.620 --> 49:56.663
We'll be right across from you.

49:56.747 --> 49:59.791
Give us a call on the radio
when you have her.

50:00.876 --> 50:03.378
- We will.
- Well, good luck.

50:06.298 --> 50:07.633
Let's go.

50:46.547 --> 50:48.173
How are they gonna
get Amanda up here?

50:49.758 --> 50:51.426
<i>Ambush! Ambush!</i>

50:51.593 --> 50:55.472
<i>Hey, Remy! Fucking Cheese!
Where is she?</i>

50:56.640 --> 51:01.478
<i>There she is.
I can see her. It ain't the way it is!</i>

51:03.063 --> 51:05.148
<i>Someone hit Cheese!</i>

51:05.858 --> 51:07.234
You sure you heard something?
Yes!

51:07.317 --> 51:08.861
- Over there!
- What happened?

51:08.944 --> 51:11.655
I don't know. I heard a splash.
Down there!

51:11.697 --> 51:12.698
Somebody took Cheese out,

51:12.781 --> 51:14.199
- and then all hell broke loose.
- Where's Amanda?

51:14.283 --> 51:15.450
- Shots were fired from over there.
- I don't know!

51:15.534 --> 51:16.535
Something went in the water!

51:16.618 --> 51:17.619
- What?
- You sure you heard something?

51:17.703 --> 51:18.996
- Yeah, something went in, but I...
- Where did it go?

51:19.079 --> 51:20.539
There! Right there!

51:20.622 --> 51:21.665
Oh, my God.

51:22.875 --> 51:24.084
Oh, no.

51:36.221 --> 51:38.140
Jesus Christ!

52:27.022 --> 52:30.275
<i>Paging
Dr. Goldsburn. Dr. Goldsburn to ICU.</i>

52:51.672 --> 52:53.882
- Hi.
- Hi.

52:55.133 --> 52:58.846
- How's the leg?
- It'll be fine.

53:02.015 --> 53:03.809
They find anything?

53:06.103 --> 53:10.941
- They got divers in there now.
- She could still be alive.

53:12.985 --> 53:16.822
Maybe she's hiding.
She could be stuck.

53:16.864 --> 53:18.073
Right?

53:20.617 --> 53:22.619
I don't think so.

53:41.138 --> 53:42.097
Hey...

53:42.181 --> 53:44.266
<i>He's ever seen
in all his years,</i>

53:44.349 --> 53:48.353
<i>on a little girl called Amanda
and a doll named Mirabelle.</i>

53:48.437 --> 53:51.440
<i>This quarry is
extremely deep and treacherous.</i>

53:52.274 --> 53:56.653
<i>All too often,
she keeps that which she takes in.</i>

53:56.695 --> 53:58.447
<i>A sad end
to that story, Suzanne.</i>

53:58.530 --> 53:59.990
<i>It sure is, Phil.</i>

54:00.407 --> 54:03.619
<i>And Ron is next with
sports. The Bruins in action tonight?</i>

54:03.702 --> 54:05.120
<i>Yes, they are, Phil.</i>

54:05.204 --> 54:06.997
<i>The B's took a crack
at the Flyers tonight,</i>

54:07.080 --> 54:09.166
<i>and the rough stuff started
in the first period.</i>

54:09.291 --> 54:12.961
<i>And like that, she was gone.</i>

54:16.173 --> 54:19.218
<i>We gave our statements.
Nick and Remy the same.</i>

54:20.719 --> 54:24.181
<i>All of us spared any blame
for Amanda's death.</i>

54:24.223 --> 54:26.141
<i>Jack Doyle resigned on the condition</i>

54:26.225 --> 54:29.353
<i>that he and he alone
be held accountable.</i>

54:29.436 --> 54:33.106
<i>The legendary captain
of a unit dedicated to children</i>

54:33.190 --> 54:35.859
<i>stepped down today
in the aftermath of controversy.</i>

54:35.901 --> 54:38.987
<i>He was granted
the dignity of early retirement.</i>

54:40.113 --> 54:42.908
<i>But the humiliation of half a pension.</i>

54:45.911 --> 54:49.540
<i>It was an ignominious end
to an illustrious career.</i>

54:50.999 --> 54:54.628
<i>Chris' run lasted a day and a half until,
from what they could tell,</i>

54:54.711 --> 54:57.714
<i>he ran into someone who wanted
the money more than he did.</i>

54:57.756 --> 54:58.757
<i>Twenty-nine-year-old
Chris Mullen</i>

54:58.841 --> 54:59.883
<i>was gunned down last night</i>

54:59.967 --> 55:01.552
<i>in an apparent robbery.</i>

55:01.593 --> 55:03.887
<i>The police commissioner
defended the rising tide of crime</i>

55:03.929 --> 55:06.807
<i>as a statistical aberration tied
to growing unemployment</i>

55:06.890 --> 55:08.892
<i>and the humidity of...</i>

55:13.856 --> 55:16.775
<i>Enough time went by
and they called off the search.</i>

55:16.859 --> 55:19.570
<i>They issued Helene
a death certificate.</i>

55:35.252 --> 55:38.672
<i>The frame and the casket were
donated by the funeral home,</i>

55:40.966 --> 55:44.303
<i>but had to be returned
at the end of the afternoon.</i>

55:47.681 --> 55:49.725
You know I love you, right?

55:49.808 --> 55:51.226
Yeah.

55:52.477 --> 55:55.272
I just wanna be alone for a while.

56:02.446 --> 56:06.491
<i>I don't know if she blamed
me or if she blamed herself.</i>

56:10.245 --> 56:12.998
