<i>I don't meet him
down Murphy's,</i>

01:20:06.181 --> 01:20:07.474
<i>he's gonna call the staties.</i>

01:20:07.558 --> 01:20:09.935
<i>He's putting a
move on you. Don't go down there.</i>

01:20:10.519 --> 01:20:12.062
<i>I can handle Patrick Kenzie.</i>

01:20:12.145 --> 01:20:13.856
<i>- This is an oath we took.
- I started this.</i>

01:20:13.939 --> 01:20:15.899
<i>- This has to be protected.
- I got things to protect, too.</i>

01:20:15.941 --> 01:20:17.025
<i>- Listen to me!
- All right, Remy.</i>

01:20:17.109 --> 01:20:19.486
<i>You leave that house,
you're an enemy to me.</i>

01:20:19.570 --> 01:20:21.905
<i>- Just trust me, all right?
- No! Trust me!</i>

01:20:21.947 --> 01:20:26.618
<i>Where I come from,
you die with your secrets!</i>

01:20:52.853 --> 01:20:55.314
How long have you known Remy?

01:20:55.355 --> 01:20:58.483
Detective Bressant? Just in...

01:20:58.567 --> 01:21:01.820
Met him through
the investigation of Amanda.

01:21:01.904 --> 01:21:03.864
- That's it?
- Yeah.

01:21:07.284 --> 01:21:09.453
How long you known Remy?

01:21:10.495 --> 01:21:11.663
What is this?

01:21:11.747 --> 01:21:14.708
They got the Internet, now, Lionel.

01:21:14.791 --> 01:21:17.127
You know how it is in town.
Everybody knows everybody.

01:21:17.211 --> 01:21:19.671
No. Everybody don't know everybody.

01:21:19.755 --> 01:21:21.381
- What're you talking about?
- Why you lying?

01:21:21.465 --> 01:21:22.466
I'm not.

01:21:22.508 --> 01:21:25.302
You bragged about taking a hard bust
on the first day we met you.

01:21:25.344 --> 01:21:26.929
- No, I didn't.
- Bullshit.

01:21:27.012 --> 01:21:29.473
You're hiding something, Lionel,
and you better fucking tell it,

01:21:29.556 --> 01:21:32.476
'cause you came to our house
and you asked us for help.

01:21:32.559 --> 01:21:34.811
And we killed ourselves
trying to save Amanda.

01:21:34.853 --> 01:21:36.688
And I know you ain't being 100%
with me right now,

01:21:36.772 --> 01:21:38.690
and it's really fucking pissing me off
that you're lying,

01:21:38.774 --> 01:21:41.235
so you better interrupt me at any time,
'cause I'm about to lose...

01:21:41.318 --> 01:21:44.196
Okay. Fine, fine. All right?
Don't have a heart attack.

01:21:45.364 --> 01:21:47.491
I haven't been honest with you.

01:21:47.574 --> 01:21:50.536
It's just not something I'm proud of.
You know?

01:21:50.619 --> 01:21:53.497
I got in a bar fight back in the day.

01:21:53.539 --> 01:21:54.790
The other guy cracked his skull.

01:21:54.873 --> 01:21:57.334
At some point,
I must've said, "I'll kill you."

01:21:57.417 --> 01:22:01.797
So they had me up for attempted.
It's my word against this other guy's.

01:22:01.880 --> 01:22:04.633
Witness testified to my version
and the jury believed him.

01:22:04.675 --> 01:22:07.594
- 'Cause he was a cop.
- Yeah, he testified for me.

01:22:07.678 --> 01:22:09.346
So you knew Detective Bressant.

01:22:09.388 --> 01:22:11.723
- It's not like we were best friends.
- But you lied.

01:22:11.765 --> 01:22:15.018
- Why did you call Remy?
- He's a cop.

01:22:15.060 --> 01:22:16.937
- That's not why you called him, Lionel.
- Come on.

01:22:17.020 --> 01:22:18.856
It's a small place.
You heard them arguing.

01:22:18.939 --> 01:22:20.524
- They were being loud.
- Who? Who... Who...

01:22:20.607 --> 01:22:25.028
So you called Remy, and you and him
took Amanda to blackmail your sister.

01:22:28.115 --> 01:22:29.825
Why would I do that?

01:22:29.867 --> 01:22:32.911
I don't know, Lionel. I really don't know.

01:22:32.995 --> 01:22:35.998
Maybe because after all the
"I put the fucking plug in the jug,"

01:22:36.081 --> 01:22:38.041
and the "count your blessings"
and the "watch your language,"

01:22:38.125 --> 01:22:40.294
you're just like everybody else.

01:22:40.377 --> 01:22:42.254
You saw a bag of money
and you wanted it.

01:22:42.337 --> 01:22:43.922
And you thought
you could get away with it.

01:22:44.006 --> 01:22:46.133
But Bea called the media
and made a big thing of it.

01:22:46.216 --> 01:22:48.594
And then she called us,
and then you were fucked.

01:22:48.635 --> 01:22:50.762
The case is closed, Patrick.
The case is closed.

01:22:50.846 --> 01:22:53.140
Coke-dealing Haitian's
a pretty easy target for a frame.

01:22:53.223 --> 01:22:54.516
- Lionel?
- Excuse me.

01:22:54.600 --> 01:22:55.642
- Look at me.
- Okay. Excuse me.

01:22:55.726 --> 01:22:57.352
You took your niece,
and you laid it off on a black guy.

01:22:57.436 --> 01:22:58.645
- Pardon me.
- Lionel, tell me what happened.

01:22:58.729 --> 01:23:00.856
Can I get some service?

01:23:00.939 --> 01:23:02.274
Yeah.

01:23:09.072 --> 01:23:10.449
What?

01:23:12.075 --> 01:23:15.204
- Three shots of Cutty and a tallboy.
- Yeah.

01:23:15.245 --> 01:23:16.747
Thank you.

01:23:18.081 --> 01:23:20.083
Just give me a second.

01:23:51.365 --> 01:23:54.326
Twenty-three years
is something, right?

01:24:06.922 --> 01:24:08.298
Go.

01:24:12.427 --> 01:24:15.639
I come up to check on Amanda.
She was alone as usual.

01:24:17.891 --> 01:24:20.435
<i>I was reading her a story
when Helene and Ray come home.</i>

01:24:20.519 --> 01:24:21.603
<i>They didn't know I was there.</i>

01:24:21.645 --> 01:24:25.190
Stop fucking yelling,
my daughter's sleeping in there.

01:24:27.359 --> 01:24:29.945
They started talking about how
they'd robbed this drug dealer.

01:24:30.028 --> 01:24:32.155
You know what he's fucking gonna do
if he finds out?

01:24:32.197 --> 01:24:33.991
What's the monkey gonna do?

01:24:34.032 --> 01:24:35.367
- Oh, you know...
- I'm not...

01:24:35.450 --> 01:24:38.620
And they were talking
about leaving the state.

01:24:38.704 --> 01:24:40.163
So I called Remy and told him.

01:24:40.205 --> 01:24:42.875
There's another drug run
up to Nashua. Taking cocaine...

01:24:42.958 --> 01:24:44.626
And then what?

01:24:48.380 --> 01:24:49.506
We took her.

01:24:52.384 --> 01:24:55.095
<i>Remy laid out this plan.
It seemed easy.</i>

01:24:55.179 --> 01:24:58.015
We take her, force Helene and Ray
to cough up the cash,

01:24:58.098 --> 01:25:00.142
then we put her back. You know?

01:25:00.225 --> 01:25:02.269
Amanda gets to spend
a weekend in the country.

01:25:02.352 --> 01:25:03.854
My sister learns a lesson.

01:25:04.229 --> 01:25:06.982
And fuck it, everybody gets paid
on top of it.

01:25:07.065 --> 01:25:10.027
I got no problem taking money
from a guy like Cheese.

01:25:10.068 --> 01:25:11.653
They were gonna handle the cops.

01:25:11.695 --> 01:25:13.947
But Bea, she went nuts.

01:25:14.031 --> 01:25:16.575
<i>Started calling the papers. Hired you.</i>

01:25:16.658 --> 01:25:18.994
Lionel don't want me coming here,
now you don't want the job?

01:25:19.036 --> 01:25:23.040
But once you found the money,
they had Amanda and the money.

01:25:23.123 --> 01:25:27.252
So they decided to set up
a fake exchange for you to witness.

01:25:27.336 --> 01:25:30.005
<i>They got Chris Mullen
to set up Cheese at the quarry.</i>

01:25:30.047 --> 01:25:33.675
15K and a chance to be the boss.

01:25:36.470 --> 01:25:38.764
<i>Cheese figured out
what was happening.</i>

01:25:38.847 --> 01:25:42.309
<i>Even though it was too late,
he started shooting.</i>

01:25:42.392 --> 01:25:44.311
<i>Panicking.</i>

01:25:46.939 --> 01:25:49.274
<i>And she just fell. I mean, she just...</i>

01:25:49.358 --> 01:25:51.026
She fell in.

01:25:52.486 --> 01:25:54.112
She's gone.

01:25:54.196 --> 01:25:56.365
It was an accident.
It was just an accident.

01:25:56.448 --> 01:25:58.659
She was your sister's kid, Lionel.

01:26:00.577 --> 01:26:04.206
- Your sister's child.
- You think I don't miss her?

01:26:04.289 --> 01:26:06.875
She was more my kid than Helene's.

01:26:07.960 --> 01:26:12.089
Last summer, Helene and Dottie
took Amanda to the beach.

01:26:12.256 --> 01:26:16.385
It was a real hot day.
Amanda fell asleep.

01:26:16.802 --> 01:26:19.346
They left her in the car
while they go off into the dunes,

01:26:19.429 --> 01:26:21.181
smoke a doobie with some guys.

01:26:21.265 --> 01:26:22.975
Two hours.

01:26:24.726 --> 01:26:27.437
Amanda literally roasted.

01:26:28.689 --> 01:26:30.190
She was three.

01:26:32.985 --> 01:26:37.239
Later on, I was holding her,
trying to help her get to sleep.

01:26:38.282 --> 01:26:42.953
My little Amanda, she was so hot.

01:26:45.163 --> 01:26:48.125
She felt like something
just come out of the oven.

01:26:49.501 --> 01:26:51.795
Like a fucking pot roast.

01:26:53.922 --> 01:26:56.258
So don't feel too sorry for my sister.

01:26:56.341 --> 01:27:00.095
Because she never gave a shit
about anyone but herself.

01:27:02.181 --> 01:27:05.017
Bartender. Open the safe. Now.

01:27:06.685 --> 01:27:10.647
Everybody needs to shut up and stay
calm. On the floor. On the floor!

01:27:10.731 --> 01:27:12.399
- Hands on your head. Do it.
- Oh, my God.

01:27:12.482 --> 01:27:14.067
Everybody stays calm,
this'll be over in a minute.

01:27:14.151 --> 01:27:17.070
Hey, do you know
whose bar this is, shithead?

01:27:17.654 --> 01:27:20.532
Or you can get wise, it's up to you.

01:27:23.243 --> 01:27:25.037
What did you say?

01:27:25.829 --> 01:27:27.831
You're a talker, huh?

01:27:27.915 --> 01:27:29.458
Just keep revving, motherfucker.

01:27:29.541 --> 01:27:31.627
Don't antagonize him.
He's got a gun.

01:27:31.710 --> 01:27:35.047
- Oh, just keep yapping away.
- I didn't say nothing.

01:27:35.130 --> 01:27:37.007
You should learn
to keep your mouth shut.

01:27:37.049 --> 01:27:38.509
Shut the fuck up,
for Christ's sake.

01:27:38.550 --> 01:27:41.303
- Just keep talking, pal.
- I didn't say nothing.

01:27:41.345 --> 01:27:42.721
Close your eyes.

01:27:42.804 --> 01:27:43.931
- Fuck!
- Remy Bressant.

01:27:44.014 --> 01:27:46.350
Amanda McCready
was taken by Remy Bressant.

01:27:46.391 --> 01:27:49.144
Oh, fuck, God. Amanda McCready
was taken by Remy Bressant!

01:27:49.186 --> 01:27:51.021
- Wait. Wait. Jesus.
- Remy Bressant.

01:27:51.104 --> 01:27:52.648
God damn it. Remy Bressant!

01:27:52.731 --> 01:27:53.815
Amanda McCready was taken

01:27:53.857 --> 01:27:55.025
- by Remy Bressant.
- Jesus. I told him.

01:27:55.067 --> 01:27:57.569
I told him we took her for ransom.
I told him. I told him, Remy.

01:27:57.653 --> 01:28:01.073
Please, I told him we took her
for ransom. I did it.

01:28:01.156 --> 01:28:03.033
Remy, please.

01:28:03.242 --> 01:28:04.743
Please.

01:28:23.011 --> 01:28:24.888
Are you all right?

01:28:26.056 --> 01:28:27.057
Stay with him.

01:29:29.453 --> 01:29:31.205
Drop your gun.

01:29:32.956 --> 01:29:34.625
Put it down!

01:29:39.379 --> 01:29:42.883
That bartender wasn't fucking around.

01:29:52.518 --> 01:29:54.061
What did you do?

01:29:54.937 --> 01:29:56.438
Did you get her killed?

01:29:59.316 --> 01:30:01.026
Say yes.

01:30:05.989 --> 01:30:07.324
Say yes.

01:30:08.242 --> 01:30:09.701
Say yes!

01:30:10.619 --> 01:30:14.790
What're you gonna do? Shoot me?
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:30:29.137 --> 01:30:31.139
She was a child.

01:30:33.308 --> 01:30:35.185
I love children.

01:31:12.055 --> 01:31:15.642
Why would I expose a conspiracy
that I was a part of?

01:31:17.060 --> 01:31:20.564
I mean, did Lionel contradict
anything I've said?

01:31:21.815 --> 01:31:25.068
Did any of the witnesses at the bar
contradict anything I've said?

01:31:25.110 --> 01:31:28.780
A police officer was killed today.
That's not looked on lightly.

01:31:28.864 --> 01:31:31.074
Is corruption looked on lightly?

01:31:31.116 --> 01:31:32.784
Is a little girl getting killed
looked on lightly?

01:31:32.868 --> 01:31:34.077
Whoa, hold on.

01:31:34.161 --> 01:31:36.622
You charge people money
as a detective.

01:31:36.663 --> 01:31:40.626
Now, you're at the quarry
the other night, right?

01:31:40.667 --> 01:31:43.587
And you have no idea
that this is a setup?

01:31:43.670 --> 01:31:46.089
You're baffled. Right?

01:31:47.633 --> 01:31:52.095
No, because, strange as it might seem,

01:31:52.137 --> 01:31:55.390
I believe the police
when they tell me something.

01:31:56.099 --> 01:31:57.309
You're a fresh prick. You know that?

01:31:57.392 --> 01:31:59.603
And because I had a ransom note
and Amanda McCready's blanket

01:31:59.686 --> 01:32:00.771
put in my mailbox.

01:32:00.854 --> 01:32:03.899
And because I read a transcript of
a call that Cheese put into the station.

01:32:03.982 --> 01:32:05.067
A 911 call?

01:32:05.150 --> 01:32:08.195
No, it was a call
Cheese made to the station.

01:32:08.278 --> 01:32:09.571
To Remy Bressant at the station.

01:32:09.655 --> 01:32:11.698
Or that Chris Mullen made,
pretending to be Cheese.

01:32:11.782 --> 01:32:13.575
Or whatever the fuck it was,
but it was recorded,

01:32:13.617 --> 01:32:15.536
and there was a call.

01:32:15.619 --> 01:32:17.538
We don't record calls
coming into the station,

01:32:17.621 --> 01:32:20.415
and we don't do transcripts, smart guy.

01:32:22.501 --> 01:32:25.087
So, did you hear a tape?

01:32:26.463 --> 01:32:28.757
- No, I didn't hear a tape.
- Okay.

01:32:28.841 --> 01:32:31.051
Did you see a transcript?

01:32:35.806 --> 01:32:38.350
No, I must've remembered it wrong.

01:32:48.610 --> 01:32:50.070
<i>Kids forgive.</i>

01:32:50.153 --> 01:32:51.655
What do they get for it?

01:32:51.697 --> 01:32:54.157
Amanda literally roasted.

01:33:03.458 --> 01:33:04.626
<i>You think I don't miss her.</i>

01:33:04.710 --> 01:33:07.171
She was more my kid than Helene's.

01:33:07.212 --> 01:33:09.339
I love children.

01:33:13.886 --> 01:33:18.098
This is the kind of thing that if you do,
Patrick, you wanna be sure.

01:33:20.392 --> 01:33:22.102
Are you sure?

01:33:22.811 --> 01:33:24.188
No.

01:33:28.025 --> 01:33:29.902
Are you coming?

01:33:30.527 --> 01:33:31.862
No.

01:33:43.498 --> 01:33:46.210
<i>Doyle brought Remy
from Louisiana back in '72.</i>

01:33:46.293 --> 01:33:49.004
<i>Care to read
the highlighted portion?</i>

01:34:00.682 --> 01:34:03.018
Taking a trip?

01:34:03.101 --> 01:34:04.853
Patrick Kenzie.

01:34:06.438 --> 01:34:09.274
To what do I owe the pleasure?

01:34:09.316 --> 01:34:11.944
Remy Bressant died last night.

01:34:12.486 --> 01:34:15.531
I was told. It's a shame.

01:34:16.949 --> 01:34:21.537
Yeah, it's hard to understand.
Because he seemed like a good man.

01:34:21.620 --> 01:34:23.455
He was a good man.

01:34:24.790 --> 01:34:27.459
We don't know
why people do what they do.

01:34:27.793 --> 01:34:30.128
Everybody looks out his own window.

01:34:30.379 --> 01:34:32.548
And everyone's got their reasons.

01:34:42.975 --> 01:34:44.643
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:34:44.726 --> 01:34:46.019
- How are you?
- Good.

01:34:46.103 --> 01:34:48.146
<i>Nick! They're firing at me.</i>

01:34:48.230 --> 01:34:49.940
Nick, you hear me? You okay?
They're firing at me!

01:34:49.982 --> 01:34:51.149
Remy!

01:34:51.233 --> 01:34:53.485
- I heard something go in the water!
- Ambush! Ambush!

01:34:53.569 --> 01:34:56.446
- Something went in!
- Run. Remy. Run!

01:34:57.239 --> 01:34:58.532
<i>Panicking.</i>

01:34:58.615 --> 01:35:01.451
<i>Amanda got scared.
She started running.</i>

01:35:01.493 --> 01:35:04.454
<i>She just fell. I mean, she just fell in.</i>

01:35:08.876 --> 01:35:10.043
<i>Twenty-nine-year-old
Chris Mullen</i>

01:35:10.127 --> 01:35:11.545
<i>was gunned down last night</i>

01:35:11.628 --> 01:35:12.880
<i>in an apparent robbery.</i>

01:35:12.963 --> 01:35:16.091
You go back inside with Frannie.
Papa will come in soon.

01:35:16.175 --> 01:35:17.301
Make you a sandwich, okay?

01:35:17.384 --> 01:35:18.635
- All right.
- That's my girl.

01:35:18.677 --> 01:35:19.720
<i>Don't go down there.</i>

01:35:19.803 --> 01:35:21.471
If I think he has the evidence,
I'll take the hit.

01:35:21.555 --> 01:35:22.681
I got no problem doing the time.

01:35:22.764 --> 01:35:25.184
Fuck up, and it's Amanda and her life.

01:35:25.267 --> 01:35:26.602
<i>All right.
I got things to protect, too.</i>

01:35:26.685 --> 01:35:28.937
<i>You leave that house,
you're an enemy to me</i>

01:35:29.021 --> 01:35:30.189
<i>and you're a danger to Amanda.</i>

01:35:30.272 --> 01:35:32.399
Please, I told him
we took her for ransom. I did it.

01:35:32.482 --> 01:35:34.526
I told him. Remy, please.

01:35:39.656 --> 01:35:40.949
So now you know.

01:35:41.825 --> 01:35:44.286
<i>My sister's not stable.
She's on crack.</i>

01:35:44.369 --> 01:35:46.455
She's talking about leaving the state.
I'm scared for my niece.

01:35:46.538 --> 01:35:48.749
- Who's gonna take care of her?
- We'll do something.

01:35:48.832 --> 01:35:50.959
<i>We'll figure it out.
She's an addict.</i>

01:35:51.043 --> 01:35:52.586
Bigot. Drug mule.

01:35:52.669 --> 01:35:55.714
The child will be dead
or on the street in 10 years.

01:35:55.797 --> 01:35:58.467
<i>What about the uncle?
He can never tell anyone.</i>

01:35:58.550 --> 01:36:01.929
<i>Not even his wife.
Or he'll never see her again.</i>

01:36:02.012 --> 01:36:06.016
<i>It's worth it to him.
Know she'll have a better life.</i>

01:36:06.058 --> 01:36:09.061
<i>Do one last good thing
before we hang it up.</i>

01:36:10.854 --> 01:36:13.899
<i>How many children
have we seen destroyed?</i>

01:36:14.900 --> 01:36:16.193
<i>Enough.</i>

01:36:17.986 --> 01:36:19.780
Does it make you feel better?

01:36:20.697 --> 01:36:24.034
Telling yourself you did it
for the right reasons?

01:36:24.076 --> 01:36:26.411
That you took her to be saved.

01:36:26.495 --> 01:36:28.372
From her own mother?

01:36:30.541 --> 01:36:33.710
We're just trying to give
a little girl a life.

01:36:34.962 --> 01:36:38.298
Wasn't your life to give.
Helene's her mother.

01:36:38.382 --> 01:36:41.093
If you thought she was a bad mother,
you should've gone to Social Services.

01:36:41.176 --> 01:36:45.097
Short of that, she's her mother,
and that's where she belongs.

01:36:46.515 --> 01:36:48.517
You turn around.

01:36:48.600 --> 01:36:52.813
You go back to your fucking car,
and you wait 30 years.

01:36:54.273 --> 01:36:56.775
You don't know
what the world is made of yet.

01:36:59.069 --> 01:37:02.155
I'm calling state police in five minutes.
They'll be here in ten.

01:37:02.239 --> 01:37:04.992
Thought you would've
done that by now.

01:37:07.327 --> 01:37:09.580
